Reasoning: The paper proposes a computer aided diagnosis tool for prostate cancer grading using whole slide images. This involves image classification and weakly-supervised ROI detection, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The model also utilizes attention-based multiple instance learning, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
